-- British Drug Company Lectus to Seek Warsaw Listing, Sunday Express Says
-- B y   M i c h e l l e   E .   F r a z e r
-- 2010-10-10T10:19:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/british-drug-company-lectus-to-seek-warsaw-listing-sunday-express-says.html
U.K. drug development firm Lectus
Therapeutics will announce its intention to list shares on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange’s NewConnect junior market, the Sunday
Express said, citing Warsaw bourse President Ludwik Sobolewski.  Sobolewski wants to increase the number of British
companies listed on NewConnect, according to the Express.
Lectus’s initial public offering “is an additional measure to
get new stakeholders and new allies,” Sobolewski told the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
